public class QueryController
extends org.springframework.web.servlet.mvc.AbstractController

The Search Service provides UICDS clients with services to discover and access work products using OpenSearch enabled feeds. The Search Service accepts queries in the following format: 

     ?productType=Incident&updatedBy=bob@core1
The table follow describes the supported query terms.
Term Description
productID The identifier of a Work Product
productType The type of a Work Product
productVersion The version of a Work Product
productState The Work Product status (Open, Closed, Archive)
createdBegin The beginning date and time of a range in which the Work Product was created
createdEnd The ending date and time of a range in which the Work Product was created
createdBy The name of the user that created the Work Product
updatedBegin The beginning date and time of a range in which the Work Product was last updated
updatedEnd The ending date and time of a range in which the Work Product was last updated
updatedBy The name of the user that last updated the Work Product
bbox A geospatial bounding box ( bbox=minX,minY,maxX,maxY ) intersecting or containing the Work Product (based on the Digest)
what The type of any "Thing" referenced within the Work Product metadata
mimetype The mimetype of the Work Product payload
The format of the results is controlled by the format parameter. For instance: 
     ?productType=Incident&updatedBy=bob@core1&format=rss
Currently supported formats:
Format Description
kml KML 2.2
w3crss RSS 2.0 with W3C Basic Geo extensions
rss RSS 2.0 with GeoRSS GML extensions
xml UICDS Work Product Format (UCore 2.0 DataItemPackage)

Author:
William Summers
See Also:
OpenSearch 1.1 Specification, RSS 2.0 Specification, GeoRSS Specification, W3C Basic Geo Vocabulary
